Ahhh la catrina all compliments: the service, the price and the atmosphere. We all had the lunch special. Mine was a tomato based soup mildly spiced with pieces of chicharon and  crisp corn taco shells. The entree was beef with chimichurrie sauce and fries, dessert was a brownie.  All, the food was great. The handsome servers was the icing on the cake.  What a delightful lunch.
